ishnuprayag and Karnaprayag. Leave early morning. Joshimath - Auli  (16 Km) 1 hr. by cab.'),(79,27,'_how_to_reach','field_58624dcae81b4'),(80,27,'best_time_to_travel','a:3:{i:0;s:6:\"Summer\";i:1;s:6:\"Autumn\";i:2;s:6:\"Winter\";}'),(81,27,'_best_time_to_travel','field_58624f87e81bc'),(82,27,'nearby_places','<strong>Joshimath: </strong>\r\n\r\nJoshimath town is one of the most interesting places in the inner Himalayan range of Garhwal. Apart from being a Tehsil and Block headquarters of administrative entities of the same names, Joshimath is also the headquarters of an army brigade and home to the Garhwal Scouts paramilitary force. But while the town of Joshimath have its own importance and significance in the realm of administration and defence, this website will be primarily focusing on the potential of Joshimath as a base camp and hub for experiencing the outstanding natural scenery and trekking potential of the adjoining areas.\r\n\r\n<strong>Shankaracharya Temple:</strong>\r\n\r\nThe town of Joshimath derives its name from the Jyotirmath. Adiguru Shankracharya was on a mission to revive Hinduism which had been eclipsed by Buddhism. At fist a Math was established by him at Joshimath and Dham at Sri Badrinath. The math established in Joshimath in the 8<sup>th</sup> century C.E., today known by the name <em>Jyotirmath</em>, has a huge mulberry tree in its precincts. This huge mulberry tree is said to be around 2400 years old and located atop a cave where Adiguru had meditated. Today hundreds of pilgrims visit Adiguru’s seat at jyotirmath to listen to the holy discourse called parvachan every evening.\r\n\r\n<strong>Badrinath:</strong>\r\n\r\nFor those on a <em>Char-Dham</em> tour, Joshimath is a suitable place for overnight stay before departure next day to <em><a href=\"http://www.dreammountain.net/badrinath/\">Sri Badrinath</a></em>, a further 40 km away. Joshimath has its historical significance in its contribution to this legendary saga of Char dhams. The magnificent scenery, climate and well socked market needed for a tourist is also one of the reasons for its developing as a major halting station for all types of tourists visiting this area.'),(83,27,'_nearby_places','field_58625080e81be'),(84,27,'weather_condition_summer','April-June. Pleasant. Maximum day temperature is around 20 degrees Celsius while night temperature comes down to 7 degrees Celsius. Carry woollens.'),(85,27,'_weather_condition_summer','field_58624ea9e81b8'),(86,27,'weather_condition_autumn','September to November. Moderately cold. Maximum day temperature is around 14 degrees Celsius while night temperature comes down to 4 degrees Celsius. Carry woollens.'),(87,27,'_weather_condition_autumn','field_58624efee81b9'),(88,27,'weather_condition_monsoon','There is no real monsoon but Auli receives rains in July-August span. Travelling is not recommended in this time of the year because of heavy land slides.'),(89,27,'_weather_condition_monsoon','field_58624f29e81ba'),(90,27,'weather_condition_winter','Auli receives regular heavy snowfalls between third week of Decemeber and last week of March. Day temperature stays between 10-13 degrees Celsius while night temperature goes 8 degrees below freezing. Must carry heavy woollens.'),(91,27,'_weather_condition_winter','field_58624f51e81bb'),(92,27,'nearest_railhead','Hardwar'),(93,27,'_nearest_railhead','field_58624e0ee81b5'),(94,27,'nearest_airport','Jolly Grant'),(95,27,'_nearest_airport','field_58624e6ae81b6'),(96,27,'nearest_bus_stop','Joshimath'),(97,27,'_nearest_bus_stop','field_58624e89e81b7'),(98,27,'staying_options','There are not many accommodation options. Cliff Top Restaurant, GMVN and Auli Resort are the main staying options available. Book early (at least 3 months before) to get confirmed booking.'),(99,27,'_staying_options','field_586250f7e81c0'),(100,27,'restaurants_and_bars','All above staying options have their own in-house restaurants and bars.'),(101,27,'_restaurants_and_bars','field_58625120e81c1'),(102,27,'marketplaces','No real market place nearby. However, if you have your own vehicle you can come down to Joshimath to get some essential items.'),(103,27,'_marketplaces','field_58625146e81c2'),(104,27,'local_culture_and_festivals','Auli is meant for skiing and tourism. Local people are Garhwalis. They have their own cultures, festivals and rituals. Nothing you would experience in Auli.'),(105,27,'_local_culture_and_festivals','field_586250bde81bf'),(106,27,'dos_and_donts','Nothing special.'),(107,27,'_dos_and_donts','field_5862504ee81bd'),(108,31,'_edit_last','1'),(109,31,'_edit_lock','1484133721:1'),(110,32,'_wp_attached_file','2017/01/Silk_route.jpg'),(111,32,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:2868;s:6:\"height\";i:1866;s:4:\"file\";s:22:\"2017/01/Silk_route.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:12:{s:8:\"aperture\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"0\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(112,31,'_thumbnail_id','32'),(113,31,'introduction','The Silk Road or Silk Route was an ancient network of trade routes that for centuries were central to cultural interaction through regions of the Asian continent connecting the East and West from China to the Mediterranean Sea. '),(114,31,'_introduction','field_58624d54e81b3'),(115,31,'how_to_reach','Old Silk Route starts from Pedong in Sikkim. Take a cab from Siliguri or New Jalpaiguri to reach Reshi (3 hours).'),(116,31,'_how_to_reach','field_58624dcae81b4'),(117,31,'best_time_to_travel','a:2:{i:0;s:6:\"Summer\";i:1;s:6:\"Autumn\";}'),(118,31,'_best_time_to_travel','field_58624f87e81bc'),(119,31,'nearby_places','Sillery Gaon, Echhe Gaon, Reshi, Pedong, Aritar Lake, Linthan, Thambi View Point, Zuluk, Gnathng Valley, Kupup Lake, Old Baba Madir, Tsong Mo, Nathu La, New Ba