eld_58624dcae81b4'),(320,50,'best_time_to_travel','a:1:{i:0;s:11:\"All seasons\";}'),(321,50,'_best_time_to_travel','field_58624f87e81bc'),(322,50,'nearby_places','<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Rajabhat Khawa:</strong> small town situated just outside the Buxa Tiger Reserve in the Alipurduar district of West Bengal, India. It is known for its natural beauty, surrounded by forest. All the permits for the entry to the Buxa Tiger reserve can be taken from here.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Buxa Fort</strong>: located at an altitude of 867 metres (2,844 ft) in the Buxa Tiger Reserve, Alipurduar district, West Bengal. It is located 30 kilometres (19 mi) from Alipurduar, the nearest town. The Bhutan King used the fort to protect the portion of famous Silk Route connecting Tibet with India, via Bhutan. Still later during unrest in Occupation of Tibet, hundreds of refugees arrived at the place and used the then abandoned fort as refuge.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Cooch Behar palace</strong>: Cooch Behar Palace, also called the Victor Jubilee Palace, is a landmark in Cooch Behar city, West Bengal. It was designed on the model of Buckingham Palace in London in 1887, during the reign of Maharaja Nripendra Narayan. The Cooch Behar Palace, noted for its elegance and grandeur, is a property of The Mantri\'s. It is a brick-built double-storey structure in the classical Western style covering an area of 51,309 square feet (4,766.8 m2). The whole structure is 395 feet (120 m) long and 296 feet (90 m) wide and is on rests 4 feet 9 inches (1.45 m) above the ground. The articles and precious objects that these rooms and halls used to contain are now lost.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Rasik bill</strong>: Rasikbil or Rasikbeel is a small lake situated in the Cooch Behar district of West Bengal, India. This lake attracts a lot of birds which make nests in the trees around the lake. The bird varieties which live in and around the lake includes cormorants, different varieties of storks, ibis, spoonbill, kingfisher, parrots, owl and many others. There is a deer park and a crocodile rehabilitation center by the side of the lake. There are also a leopard house, a python house, Aviary &amp; a Tortoise rescue entre.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(323,50,'_nearby_places','field_58625080e81be'),(324,50,'weather_condition_summer','Hot and humid. Must take necessary care about mosquito bites as they carry malignant malaria at this time of the year. In case of any sudden fever or unusual behaviour consult local doctor immediately.'),(325,50,'_weather_condition_summer','field_58624ea9e81b8'),(326,50,'weather_condition_autumn','Hot and humid. You may experience occasional rainfall between October and November which brings down temperature to a certain degrees. No need to carry woollens.'),(327,50,'_weather_condition_autumn','field_58624efee81b9'),(328,50,'weather_condition_monsoon','Receives moderate to heavy rainfall between end of June and mid of September. The best time to visit the forest to experience its lush green mesmerising beauty. '),(329,50,'_weather_condition_monsoon','field_58624f29e81ba'),(330,50,'weather_condition_winter','Usually pleasant. Temperature stays between 22 deg. Celsius (day) and 10 deg. Celsius (night). However, at times temperature may come down. Light woollens are recommended.'),(331,50,'_weather_condition_winter','field_58624f51e81bb'),(332,50,'nearest_railhead','Alipurduar Junction / New Alipurduar (37 Km)'),(333,50,'_nearest_railhead','field_58624e0ee81b5'),(334,50,'nearest_airport','Bagdogra (195 Km)'),(335,50,'_nearest_airport','field_58624e6ae81b6'),(336,50,'nearest_bus_stop','Alipurduar (35 Km)'),(337,50,'_nearest_bus_stop','field_58624e89e81b7'),(338,50,'staying_options','The best staying option could be the Cottages of West Bengal Tourism (WBTDC) available inside Buxa forest. Book early to avoid heavy rush. Apart from this you would get private hotels outside the forest as well.'),(339,50,'_staying_options','field_586250f7e81c0'),(340,50,'restaurants_and_bars','Restaurants are available outside the forest. No so-called bar is available nearby.'),(341,50,'_restaurants_and_bars','field_58625120e81c1'),(342,50,'marketplaces','Buxa forest is a popular tourist destination. You would get necessary goods nearby. For bigger market places you have to go to Alipurduar town bus stand (35 Km)'),(343,50,'_marketplaces','field_58625146e81c2'),(344,50,'local_culture_and_festivals','Languages spoken: Bengali, Hindi, English and Bhutanese\r\nDominant religions: Hindu, Buddhist, Mulsims\r\n'),(345,50,'_local_culture_and_festivals','field_586250bde81bf'),(346,50,'dos_and_donts','Not applicable'),(347,50,'_dos_and_donts','field_5862504ee81bd'),(348,50,'display_on_hompage','Yes'),(349,50,'_display_on_hompage','field_586c742fef5b7'),(350,50,'view_count','150'),(351,50,'_view_count','field_586f38d6263cc'),(352,50,'place_photo_1','55'),(353,50,'_place_photo_1','field_586f8dbdab09a'),(354,50,'place_photo_2','54'),(355,50,'_place_photo_2','field_586f8e38ab09c'),(356,50,'place_photo_3','52'),(357,50,'_place_photo_3','field_586f8e58ab09d'),(358,50,'place_photo_4','53'),(359,50,'_place_photo_4','field_586f8e71ab09e'),(363,58,'_edit_last','1'),(364,58,'_edit_lock','1484060202:1'),(365,59,'_wp_attached_file','2017/01/1446232223_dsc_0193_1_2.jpg'),(366,59,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:960;s:6:\"height\";i:539;s:4:\"file\";s:35:\"2017/01/1446232223_dsc_0193_1_2.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:12:{s:8:\"aperture\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"credit\";s:0:\"\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"0\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(367,59,'_wp_attachment_image_alt','Naini Lake'),(368,60,'_wp_attached_file','2017/01/Naina-Peak-4.jpg'),(369,60,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:1600;s:6:\"height\";i:900;s:4:\"file\";s:24:\"2017/01/Naina-Pea