on\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"0\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(379,63,'_wp_attachment_image_alt','Naini Lake'),(380,58,'_thumbnail_id','59'),(381,58,'introduction','Blessed with its own scenic lake, Nainital is a hill station surrounded by the peaks of Kumaon Hills and is full of natural hot water springs. Nainital is divided into two parts, Tallital and Mallital, with the lake separating them.  Tallital is the southern side of the lake, while Mallital consists of the northern upper reaches.'),(382,58,'_introduction','field_58624d54e81b3'),(383,58,'how_to_reach','Nainital is well connected by road from Delhi and Kathgodam in Haldwani district of Uttarakhand. Plenty of trains connect this place with Delhi and Dehradun. Passengers coming from Kolkata, Lucknow, Agra and Mathura, can even take a train till Kathgodam and then hire a private cab or shared taxi for Nainital. Daily overnight Volvo and City bus services are available from Delhi as well. Distance of Nainital from Kathgodam is only 24 Km while Delhi is 288 Km away.'),(384,58,'_how_to_reach','field_58624dcae81b4'),(385,58,'best_time_to_travel','a:3:{i:0;s:6:\"Summer\";i:1;s:6:\"Autumn\";i:2;s:6:\"Winter\";}'),(386,58,'_best_time_to_travel','field_58624f87e81bc'),(387,58,'nearby_places','<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Naini Lake (4 Km):</strong> Nainital Lake, famously known as Naini Lake is the major attraction of Naintal town as well of Uttarakhand.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Nainital Zoo (1.8 Km):</strong> Nainital Zoo is one of the best attraction for wildlife lovers in Nainital. Officially named as Bharat Ratna Pt. Govind   Ballabh Pant High Altitude Zoo.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Naina Devi Temple (2.5 Km):</strong> A well known Shakti Peeths of Hindu religion, Naini Devi Temple is sacred place of great devotion in Nainital</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Echo Cave Park (4 Km):</strong> Eco Cave Gardens is a newly developed tourist spot in Nainital. It comprises several natural inter connected caves of different animals</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Snow View Point (4 Km):</strong> Snow View Point is one of the most visited places by tourists for watching majestic Himalayas from Nainital</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Naina Peak (7 Km):</strong> Naina Peak is highest hill top and one of the the famous tourist spots in Nainital. This peak is also called as China Peak and Cheena Peak by locals.</li>\r\n</ul>'),(388,58,'_nearby_places','field_58625080e81be'),(389,58,'weather_condition_summer','May to Mid of July. Average day time temperature recorded in this period of the year is 21 degree Celsius while average night temperature is recorded 15 degree Celsius. This is a good time to visit Nainital. Ideally no woollen is required.'),(390,58,'_weather_condition_summer','field_58624ea9e81b8'),(391,58,'weather_condition_autumn','Mid September to mid November. Average day time temperature recorded in this period of the year is 19 degree Celsius while average night temperature is recorded 13 degree Celsius. This is a good time to visit Nainital. Light to moderate woollen is recommended specially for people staying at planes.'),(392,58,'_weather_condition_autumn','field_58624efee81b9'),(393,58,'weather_condition_monsoon','July to mid October. Moderate to heavy rainfalls are recorded in this time of the year. With rainfalls temperature also comes down. Average day time temperature recorded in this period of the year is 17 degree Celsius while average night temperature is recorded 9 degree Celsius. Because of heavy landslide prone areas visiting Nanital within this period is not recommended.'),(394,58,'_weather_condition_monsoon','field_58624f29e81ba'),(395,58,'weather_condition_winter','Mid October to April. Average day time temperature recorded in this period of the year is 11.5 degree Celsius while average night temperature is recorded 4.5 degree Celsius. This is a good time to visit Nainital. Light to moderate woollen is recommended specially for people staying at planes.'),(396,58,'_weather_condition_winter','field_58624f51e81bb'),(397,58,'nearest_railhead','Kathgodam'),(398,58,'_nearest_railhead','field_58624e0ee81b5'),(399,58,'nearest_airport','New Delhi'),(400,58,'_nearest_airport','field_58624e6ae81b6'),(401,58,'nearest_bus_stop','Nainital Lake / Nainital Town'),(402,58,'_nearest_bus_stop','field_58624e89e81b7'),(403,58,'staying_options','There are plenty of staying options available at Nainital itself. Most of the hotels and lodges are situated at the gradient of hills surrounding the Naini Lake, the main attraction of this place. Unlike other hill station, winter is not a declared off-season at Nainital. Rooms rates may go higher in this season as many tourists come to enjoy snowfall, although this is not a regular phenomena of Nainital. If you are not a group of large number of people, hotels and lodges are available on spot.'),(404,58,'_staying_options','field_586250f7e81c0'),(405,58,'restaurants_and_bars','Many hotels and lodges have their own restaurants and bars. However, there are plenty of road side restaurants are bars available as well.'),(406,58,'_restaurants_and_bars','field_58625120e81c1'),(407,58,'marketplaces','Nainital itself has a fairly large market for tourists to collect their mementos and other necessary items. '),(408,58,'_marketplaces','field_58625146e81c2'),(409,58,'local_culture_and_festivals','Because the place is located at the foothills of Kumaon Himalaya the majority of local people are Kumaoni. Languages spoken are Hindi, English and Kumaoni.'),(410,58,'_local_culture_and_festivals','field_586250bde81bf'),(411,58,'dos_and_donts','The local authority of Nainital is very strict and watchful. You may be fined for leaving your wastes in lakes or on road. Smoking in public is completely banned. You may be fined up to Rs. 2000.'),(412,58,'_dos_and_donts','field_5862504e