ield_58624d54e81b3'),(1136,141,'how_to_reach','Amritsar is a major city of India and is well connected via air, road and railways from almost every part of the country.  You can come to Amritsar by train from all major cities like Delhi, Mumbai, Chennai, Hyderabad, Ahmedabad, Kolkata, Agra, and Chandigarh. '),(1137,141,'_how_to_reach','field_58624dcae81b4'),(1138,141,'best_time_to_travel','a:1:{i:0;s:11:\"All seasons\";}'),(1139,141,'_best_time_to_travel','field_58624f87e81bc'),(1140,141,'nearby_places','<ul>\r\n 	<li>Golden Temple (City)</li>\r\n 	<li>Durgiana Temple (City)</li>\r\n 	<li>Mata Temple (City)</li>\r\n 	<li>Jallianwalah Bagh (City)</li>\r\n 	<li>Khalsa College (City)</li>\r\n 	<li>Attari-Wagah Border: 32 Km</li>\r\n 	<li>Pathankot: 116 Km</li>\r\n 	<li>Chandigarh: 192 Km</li>\r\n 	<li>Dalhousie: 198 Km</li>\r\n 	<li>Dharamsala: 202 Km</li>\r\n 	<li>New Delhi: 463 Km</li>\r\n</ul>'),(1141,141,'_nearby_places','field_58625080e81be'),(1142,141,'weather_condition_summer','April to July. Very hot in summer. Day temperature can go up to 45 degrees Celsius and night temperature stays around 39 degrees.'),(1143,141,'_weather_condition_summer','field_58624ea9e81b8'),(1144,141,'weather_condition_autumn','March to April. Not as hot as summer but temperature stays between 38 and 28 in days and nights.'),(1145,141,'_weather_condition_autumn','field_58624efee81b9'),(1146,141,'weather_condition_monsoon','July to mid of September. Amritsar gets fair amount of rain in this period.'),(1147,141,'_weather_condition_monsoon','field_58624f29e81ba'),(1148,141,'weather_condition_winter','October to February. Winter is from moderately cold to chilled cold. The lifetime minimum temperature recorded so far is 3.7 degrees below freezing what happened in January in the year 1933.'),(1149,141,'_weather_condition_winter','field_58624f51e81bb'),(1150,141,'nearest_railhead','Amritsar'),(1151,141,'_nearest_railhead','field_58624e0ee81b5'),(1152,141,'nearest_airport','Raja sansi'),(1153,141,'_nearest_airport','field_58624e6ae81b6'),(1154,141,'nearest_bus_stop','Amritsar ISBT'),(1155,141,'_nearest_bus_stop','field_58624e89e81b7'),(1156,141,'staying_options','Amritsar is a fairly large and highly popular city of India with many hotels and lodges available here ranging from low cost to star type accommodations. You can find accommodation in any time of the year even if you haven\'t pre-booked any.'),(1157,141,'_staying_options','field_586250f7e81c0'),(1158,141,'restaurants_and_bars','Being a busy and popular city and a major tourist attraction one can find many of these kinds scattered around the city. Kesar ka Dhaba, The Yellow Chilli, Kanha Sweets and Bharawan ka Dhaba are few of many famous restaurants in Amritsar where you can enjoy your food with your family and friends.'),(1159,141,'_restaurants_and_bars','field_58625120e81c1'),(1160,141,'marketplaces','Amritsar itself is a large market place. You can find many small and big market areas in and around the city. Katra Jaimal Singh is one of the best textile markets in the city. Other than this Shahid Bhagat Singh market, Shimla Market, Kennedy Avenue market are also come in the major and popular markets\' list.'),(1161,141,'_marketplaces','field_58625146e81c2'),(1162,141,'local_culture_and_festivals','The chief festivals celebrated at Amritsar comprise Vaisakhi, Lohri, Guru Parb and Holi. Vaisakhi or Baisakhi is the festival celebrated in the holy memory of the foundation anniversary of Khalsa Panth. Khalsa was established in the year 1699 at Anandpur Sahib by Guru Govind Singh. Lohri is the harvest festival celebrated on 13th January. Guru Parb is organized in the months of November and January. Hola Mohalla is a unique festival celebrated at Anandpur to pay homage to to Guru Govind Singh.'),(1163,141,'_local_culture_and_festivals','field_586250bde81bf'),(1164,141,'available_tour_packages','a:1:{i:0;s:3:\"155\";}'),(1165,141,'_available_tour_packages','field_587861d2833f5'),(1166,141,'dos_and_donts','Apart from being am advanced city Amritsar is also a holy place as well. People here are mostly Sikhs and they are very strict and conscious about  their religion. Don\'t forget to cover your head with a specially piece of cloth when you enter the hole Golden Temple. Be very careful about throwing your left overs here and there, you will definitely get noticed. Sikhs are all non-smokers. However, they will not stop you from doing it but do not even try to smoke as you approach close to the temple'),(1167,141,'_dos_and_donts','field_5862504ee81bd'),(1168,141,'place_photo_1','142'),(1169,141,'_place_photo_1','field_586f8dbdab09a'),(1170,141,'place_photo_2','144'),(1171,141,'_place_photo_2','field_586f8e38ab09c'),(1172,141,'place_photo_3','145'),(1173,141,'_place_photo_3','field_586f8e58ab09d'),(1174,141,'place_photo_4','147'),(1175,141,'_place_photo_4','field_586f8e71ab09e'),(1176,141,'location_map','a:3:{s:7:\"address\";s:58:\"Golden Temple, Golden Temple Road, Amritsar, Punjab, India\";s:3:\"lat\";s:17:\"31.61998029999999\";s:3:\"lng\";s:17:\"74.87648489999992\";}'),(1177,141,'_location_map','field_58760b5e5b7e7'),(1178,141,'display_on_hompage','Yes'),(1179,141,'_display_on_hompage','field_586c742fef5b7'),(1180,141,'view_count','17'),(1181,141,'_view_count','field_586f38d6263cc'),(1182,148,'_edit_last','1'),(1183,148,'_edit_lock','1484928123:1'),(1184,149,'_wp_attached_file','2017/01/Dharamsala-1.jpg'),(1185,149,'_wp_attachment_metadata','a:4:{s:5:\"width\";i:700;s:6:\"height\";i:512;s:4:\"file\";s:24:\"2017/01/Dharamsala-1.jpg\";s:10:\"image_meta\";a:12:{s:8:\"aperture\";s:1:\"0\";s:6:\"credit\";s:6:\"Picasa\";s:6:\"camera\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"caption\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"created_timestamp\";s:1:\"0\";s:9:\"copyright\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"focal_length\";s:1:\"0\";s:3:\"iso\";s:1:\"0\";s:13:\"shutter_speed\";s:1:\"0\";s:5:\"title\";s:0:\"\";s:11:\"orientation\";s:1:\"0\";s:8:\"keywords\";a:0:{}}}'),(1186,150,'_wp_attached_file','2017/01/flash1404091097.jpg'),(1187,150,'