m getting  confused with so many places in hand. I want to leave early on Friday and want to be at home by Sunday night so that I can resume my work from Monday of preceding week.\n\nI don\'t want to spend much time on road. It would great if I can reach my destination within 5 hours from home. Looking for your suggestions.','Looking for the best weekend destination near Kolkata','','publish','closed','closed','','looking-for-the-best-weekend-destination-near-kolkata','','','2017-01-27 13:11:25','2017-01-27 13:11:25','',184,'http://local.tourplanner.com/forums/topic/looking-for-the-best-weekend-destination-near-kolkata/',0,'topic','',0),(197,6,'2017-01-27 13:32:34','2017-01-27 13:32:34','Hello all,\n\nPlease suggest me the best time to arrange a trip for Delhi, Jaipur, Agra, Mathura, Vrindavan. I want to experience the Taj under a full moon!','What is the best time to visit Agra','','publish','closed','closed','','what-is-the-best-time-to-visit-agra','','','2017-01-27 13:32:34','2017-01-27 13:32:34','',168,'http://local.tourplanner.com/forums/topic/what-is-the-best-time-to-visit-agra/',0,'topic','',0),(198,6,'2017-01-27 13:36:43','2017-01-27 13:36:43','I want to trek Kuwari Pass via Ghat and return via Auli-Joshimath. My question is whether it is OK to go there in the month of September. I have heard that monsoon ends early in September so if I plan for last week of this month will this be a good pick? Apart from rainfall what other risk factors could be there in this time of the year?','Is September the right time to trek Kuwari Pass?','','publish','closed','closed','','is-september-the-right-time-to-trek-kuwari-pass','','','2017-01-27 13:36:43','2017-01-27 13:36:43','',179,'http://local.tourplanner.com/forums/topic/is-september-the-right-time-to-trek-kuwari-pass/',0,'topic','',0),(199,6,'2017-01-30 11:07:47','2017-01-30 11:07:47','Pin Parvati is not a trek for those new to trekking. Prior experience of a high altitude Trek is essential. By that, we mean a trek of 